	<item>
		<title>Court adjourns Mutinta’s contempt case to Wednesday</title>
		<link>https://staging.themastonline.com/2017/02/22/court-adjourns-mutintas-contempt-case-to-wednesday/</link>
		<pubDate>Wed, 22 Feb 2017 09:48:02 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[mast-admin]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">https://staging.themastonline.com/?p=16</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[ORACLE Media proprietor Mutinta M'membe's contempt case was yesterday adjourned to February 22 because the magistrate handling the matter was unwell.

Mutinta, Dr Fred M'membe's wife, was summoned to a complaint of contempt of court for allegedly tearing a search warrant on February 15.

Mutinta was supposed to appear before magistrate Ireen Wishimanga to answer to a complaint of contempt of court but the court was not available for the matter to proceed.

However, she appeared before magistrate Albert Mwaba who adjourned the case to Wednesday.

Mutinta was last Wednesday arrested by police on alleged obstruction charges when state police raided their house at the instruction of State House backed Lewis Mosho.

On Friday, Mutinta was released on a K3,000 bail after pleading not guilty to obstruction charges.]]></content:encoded>
